### CubCloud Worker Offerings (3 Distinct Projects)

| Project | Port | Type | Benchmark | Gitea Repo | Coolify |
|---------|------|------|-----------|------------|---------|
| **zesty-worker-service** | :8990 | HTTP single-shot LLM | 8% (Qwen3-Coder) | jzest/zesty-worker-service | Yes |
| **cw-worker** | :8002 | Full agentic cc-mirror | 92.3% (250 runs) | jzest/cw-worker | Yes |
| **cubcode** | N/A | CLI installer for team | N/A | jzest/cubcode | N/A |

**zesty-worker-service** — Lightweight HTTP API. Sends single LLM call through Bifrost, returns structured response. Good for simple completions, embeddings, classification. OpenAI-compatible.

**cw-worker** — Full Claude Code CLI (cc-mirror) in a Docker container. Spawns autonomous agent that writes files, runs pytest, iterates on failures. Returns code + test results. Called by LangGraph bears as a tool. 30min timeout per task.

**cubcode** — CLI distribution package. Team members clone from Gitea, run install.sh, get full Claude Code environment pointing at CubCloud GPUs via cc-router + Bifrost.

### Service Discovery
```bash
# Find all services
ssh cubby@10.10.20.10 "netstat -tlnp | grep -E '(8990|8002|8989|3200|9090|3000)'"

# Container inspection
ssh cubby@10.10.20.10 "docker ps --format 'table {{.Names}}\t{{.Image}}\t{{.Ports}}\t{{.Status}}'"

# Check both worker services
curl http://10.10.20.10:8990/health  # zesty-worker-service
curl http://10.10.20.10:8002/health  # cw-worker
```

## GPU Layout (bwh200server:10.10.20.12)

### Physical Configuration: 948GB Total VRAM
```
GPU 0,1 (H200 NVL TP=2): sglang-coding — Qwen3-Coder-Next-FP8 :30000 [systemd]
GPU 2 (H200 NVL):         sglang-vl-quality — Qwen2.5-VL-72B-Instruct-FP8 :30004 [systemd]
GPU 3 (H200 NVL):         sglang-general — Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct-FP8 :30006 [systemd]
GPU 4 (RTX PRO):          sglang-coder2 — Qwen2.5-Coder-32B-Instruct :30007 [systemd]
GPU 5 (RTX PRO):          sglang-chat — Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct :30002 [systemd]
GPU 6 (RTX PRO):          sglang-embedding — Qwen3-Embedding-8B :30003 [systemd] + kokoro-tts :8880 [docker]
GPU 7 (RTX PRO):          sglang-vl-fast — Qwen3-VL-30B-A3B :30005 [systemd]
```
All 7 sglang services now managed via systemd. Only kokoro-tts remains Docker-only.
Restart any service: `ssh cubby@10.10.20.12 "sudo systemctl restart sglang-<name>"`

