## Security Considerations

### Network Security
- FortiClient VPN or Tailscale required for external access
- Physical LAN (10.10.20.x) for direct service communication
- WireGuard mesh (10.100.0.0/24) active between servers — port 51820
  - mgmt-server: 10.100.0.1, gpu-server: 10.100.0.2
  - Brandon (CTO): 10.100.0.50 (reserved)
  - Infisical accessed via WireGuard: http://10.100.0.1:8443
- No direct internet exposure of GPU services

### Credential Security
- Secrets stored in Infisical at http://10.100.0.1:8443 (self-hosted, Docker on mgmt-server)
- Machine identity: `/etc/.env.infisical` on both servers (deployed by Ansible)
- Token auto-renewal: `infisical-token-renewal.timer` on both servers (55min cycle)
- Token cache: `/etc/infisical-cache/current-token` (root-only, 0600)
- No hardcoded credentials in source code
- Rotate tokens via Infisical UI or `infisical-token-helper`

### Access Control
- SSH key authentication only (ed25519)
- cubby user: needs password (`broadway102`) for sudo on .10, passwordless sudo on .12
- brandon user: sudo on both servers (created Phase 18 onboarding)
- All 7 sglang services managed via systemd (restart: `systemctl restart sglang-*`)
- Service-specific authentication tokens via Bifrost virtual keys

